reviews.review_text: man smart, woman smarter thats right the women are smarter......good show...a+ on paper
like it was yesterday i had such a wonderful time at this show.... can reach out and TASTE that kind that opened my eyes.

Walton, Bird and McHale! This was a pretty good show. Musically speaking I'd give it about 3,1/2 stars. Overall excitement and energy I'd give it a 4 star review. Best part for me, Kenny Coulson and Koz, (RIP) was the 90 MPH "TRIP" there leaving Albany at 4:40 p/m for the 173 mile trek through rush hour traffic out the Mass Pike onto 495 E!! We pulled into a parking lot at 7:55 p/m only to walk right up to a stretch limo as it pulled into the loading ramp, backstage to literally bump into Bill Walton, Larry bird and Kevin McHale, with whom we patted backs and shook hands! God, we miss you! PS.
